survey.automatic_detection_helpful_explanation: I felt like I was missing it when the automatic detection was gone. So yes it felt very helpful because it showed me many that were indeed anomalies. But I can imagine I missed more anomalies that were not lighted red because I was paying too much attention to the red lighted events.
survey.history_helpful_explanation: I used it to check the pattern again. Sometimes I got lost in the patterns, because you get unsure whether it's an anomaly or you just forgot what the pattern was. So the history gave me a quick visual of the pattern to be ably to detect an anomaly faster. However, it also took some space from the whole view, so I did feel more stresful in the end.
